name: Memory box #13
description:
Medium sized memory box. Each box is made one-at-a-time. The figure on the box top is entirely hand built - I use no molds and sculpt each one by hand.

The box has a winged Greyhound design on two sides, top and inside.

The box was glazed with a satin crackle green glaze. The figure was glazed with antique parchment cream glaze. This is a one of a kind piece.

I made this box with the intention that it be a memory box -- a special place to put my old Greyhound's tags, a lock of hair, etc. -- after he was no longer with me, but it could used for a urn for cremains if you choose. This box will hold approximately 4 cups. For more information about how much each box holds visit my blog http://greyhoundsculptor.com/2009/01/24/sizes/

Dimensions: 
Total exterior height ~ about 7 1/2 inches. 
Box itself ~ Exterior: about 4 3/4 inches high x 8 inches wide x 4 1/4 inches deep.

The lid of this box slightly warped during the firing. Price reflects this.

This box is handmade of clay by me, Sarah Regan Snavely, in my North Dakota studio. Artist signed. Check out my website at www.SarahReganSnavely.com and email me with any questions about my work!

name: Tall Scottish Deerhound on cream and green box
description:
This is one of my medium memory box designs featuring the Scottish Deerhound. Each box is made one-at-a-time with attention, love and work. This Deerhound at the box top is entirely hand built - I use no molds and sculpt each one by hand.

The box has running Deerhounds among dots wrapping around the sides of the box. 

The exterior of the box was glazed with a clear glossy crackle glaze over black and green. The clay body is a rich cream color. The figure at the box top is a glossy antique gray glaze. Interior of the box is worn denim blue. This is a one of a kind piece.

I made this box with the intention that it be a memory box -- a special place to put my old Greyhound's tags, a lock of hair, etc. -- after he was no longer with me, but it could used for a urn for cremains if you choose. This box will hold approximately 4-5 cups. Please check your size requirements if the intended purchase is to hold cremains. For more information about how much each box holds visit my blog http://greyhoundsculptor.com/2009/01/24/sizes/

Dimensions: 
Total exterior height ~ about 14 3/4 inches. 
Box itself ~ Exterior: about 10 1/2 inches high x 4 inches wide x 4 inches length.

This box is handmade of clay by me, Sarah Regan Snavely, in my North Dakota studio. Artist signed. Check out my website at www.SarahReganSnavely.com and email me with any questions about my work!
